  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 19.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Follow me",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; come ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "ye after me",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (Revised Version); ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "δεῦτε ὀπίσω μου",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". There is no thought of continuous following from place to place (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἀκολουθεῖν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") , but of immediate detachment from the present sphere of their interest and of attachment to Jesus as their leader. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And I will make you fishers of men",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; Mark, \"to become fishers of men,\" laying more stress on the change in their character necessary for success in this new kind of fishing. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 5:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " brings out the change in the nature of the work(",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἀπὸ τοῦ νῦν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "Fishers.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The word suggests care, patience, skill, besides habits of life fitted for endurance of privation and fatigue. The same promise is, as it seems, related in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 5:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where notice: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "note_emph",
        "text": "(1)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " It is connected with the miracle of the draught of fishes. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "note_emph",
        "text": "(2)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " It is not verbally identical with this: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "Μὴ φοβοῦ ἀπὸ τοῦ νῦν ἀνθρώπους",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἔσῃ ζωγρῶν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
